      "content": "Here's a continuation of the dialogue:\n\n\"I've been talking to the Watson boy, and I'm starting to think he's getting a little too big for his britches,\" said Mr. Jenkins, leaning in. \"Always talking about civil rights and whatnot. We need to make sure he understandes where his place is.\"\n\n\"I've had dealings with him, too,\" said Mr. Harris, \"his father's been getting a little too involved in the NAACP lately. We can't have him spreading those ideas around town. It's just not right.\"\n\n\"Setting boundaries, that's what we need to do,\" said Chief Wilson, nodding in agreement. \"Social boundaries. You know, remind the young folks that there's a reason for customs and traditions. It's for their own good, after all. We're just trying to preserve the local way of life here.\"\n\nIn this addition, the men discuss a specific issue and frame their concerns as a need to protect the local community and preserve its traditions, using language that implies a sense of paternalistic duty and concern for the well-being of the town and its residents.",
